cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper discusses a phenomenon related to deep neural networks (DNNs) with batch normalization (BN) and rectified linear activation functions, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to address the issue, which falls under the category of optimization techniques in machine learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on classification and object detection tasks, which are related to natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
